<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>An iconic song by Fleetwood Mac is soaring up the Australian charts thanks to a TikTok video showing a man 'vibin' on a skateboard. </p>

<p>The viral video, uploaded by user <?php echo e('@'); ?>420doggface208 on September 26, shows Nathan Apodaca riding along an empty highway while drinking juice and mouthing the lyrics to Dreams.</p>

<p>The clip has garnered more than 16.2million views on the social media platform, and reshuffled Spotify charts worldwide. </p>

<p>'Vibe King': A TikTok video of someone skateboarding to Fleetwood Mac's Dreams has gone viral, sending the song soaring back up the charts </p>

<p>The 1977 hit is now ranked 46th in Australia - jumping from number 54 the day the 'Vibe King's' video was uploaded and 93rd on September 25.</p>

<p>In the week prior to the video's release, Dreams averaged the position of 100 on Australia's Spotify chart.</p>

<p>The soar is similar to the United States, with the song jumping from 145 on September 25 to 24 on September 28. </p>

<p>It even moved from 50 to 32 in New Zealand on the respective dates.</p>

<p>Nathan has since been crowned 'Uncle TikTok', 'Jesus' and 'Vibe King', and said he could not believe the reaction he has had.</p>

<p>'After I did that video, as you guys know the sh<em>t went viral – holy sheep sh</em>t,' he said in a follow up video.</p>

<p>High on the charts! The 1977 hit is now ranked 46th in Australia - jumping from number 54 the day the 'Vibe King's' video was released and 93rd on September 25. Pictured: Stevie Nicks performing with Fleetwood Mac in Berkeley, California, in 1977</p>

<p>Unexpected response! Nathan (pictured) has since been crowned 'Uncle TikTok', 'Jesus' and 'Vibe King', and said he could not believe the reaction he had</p>

<p>'I just want to say thank you from the bottom of my heart from DoggFace, me and my family, to all you guys.</p>

<p>'No words that come to mind ... just overnight sh*t's been crazy,' he continued.</p>

<p>'Thank you all for the donations, thank you all for the comments, thank you all for the gifts. I just appreciate everybody.'  </p>

<p>Mammoth attention: Nathan's video has attracted the likes of high-profile YouTubers Alonzo Lerone, LLusion, Cole Walliser and Celina Spooky Boo. Pictured: A number of high-profile YouTubers and TikTokers commenting on the post</p>

<p>Nathan's video has attracted the likes of high-profile YouTubers Alonzo Lerone, LLusion, Cole Walliser and Celina Spooky Boo.</p>

<p>It was also re-shared by Fleetwood Mac on Twitter.</p>

<p>'We love this!' the page's caption read when re-sharing his video. </p>

<p>First for everything! The video (pictured) was even shared by the Fleetwood Mac Twitter page</p>
